## DISCLAIMER - ENGINEERING SOFTWARE

This software performs engineering calculations for internal combustion engines
based on established scientific formulas and peer-reviewed literature.

**IMPORTANT NOTICES:**

1. **Educational and Professional Use:**
   This software is intended for educational purposes and professional
   engineering analysis. All calculations are based on theoretical models
   and should be validated against real-world testing.

2. **No Warranty for Accuracy:**
   While every effort has been made to ensure the accuracy of formulas
   and calculations, the authors make no warranty regarding the precision
   of results. Users are responsible for validating all calculations.

3. **Not a Substitute for Professional Engineering:**
   This software does not replace professional engineering judgment and
   should not be the sole basis for critical design decisions.

4. **References and Citations:**
   All formulas are based on recognized scientific literature including:
   - Heywood, J.B. "Internal Combustion Engine Fundamentals" (1988)
   - Blair, G.P. "Design and Simulation of Four-Stroke Engines" (1999)
   - Pulkrabek, W.W. "Engineering Fundamentals of ICE" (2003)
   - Various SAE Papers and technical standards

5. **User Responsibility:**
   Users assume all responsibility for the application of results
   obtained from this software. Always consult with qualified engineers
   and perform appropriate testing and validation.

## SCIENTIFIC VALIDATION

All calculations have been validated against published literature and
industry standards. See docs/technical/REFERENCES.md for complete
bibliography and validation reports.

